## Code Quality Standards

### TypeScript
- Prefer TypeScript over JavaScript
- Include helpful comments
- Use proper types, avoid `any`

### React/Next.js
- Follow React Best Practices skill guidelines
- Use Server Components by default
- Optimize for performance from the start

### Frontend Design
- Avoid generic aesthetics (see Frontend Design skill)
- Choose distinctive fonts and color palettes
- Add meaningful animations and micro-interactions
- Create cohesive, memorable interfaces

### Research Tools
- Always check API key availability before using tools
- Implement proper error handling and rate limiting
- Log API costs and usage
- Export data to `output/` directory

